<dl id="n38173a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n38" href="#n38173a">N38 (VI.B.32)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n38all.htm#n38173a"> 173(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> mole</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">&ldquo;The Lazzaroni <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> sleep on the steps of the church doors, or in the street. Their favourite spot, however is the Largo di Castello; there they literally swarm, and pass the whole day <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> listening to some ragged fellow near <mark>the Mole</mark> <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font>&rdquo; <font color="green">[This part of Naples is mentioned a number of times in this section of the book.]</font> <small> S.M. Ellis, <a name="ELMK" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ELMK"><cite title="source">The Life of Michael Kelly</cite></a>,(1930) 41</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
